form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony, N-4-4-5-4-4-4-5

full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/21/2023 U.S. Department of Justice OMB #1115-0052 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony Naturalization and Citizenship Branch 300 NORTH LOS ANGELES STREET File or A # A 71 807 945 LOS ANGELES CA 90012 12/22/1998 Date You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony at the DATE, TIME AND PLACE SHOWN BELOW. 945 Date 12/29/1998 EFIGENIA MURILLO DE BUIFARRO Time 12:30 PM CORBIN AVE CANOBA PARK CA 91306 Place You must bring the following with you: This letter, with ALL of the QUESTIONS ON THE REVERSE side answered in ink or on a typewriter. Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. Any immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD (children), BRING your CHILD (children). Bx81 If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, please use the return address in the extreme upper left hand corner of this letter. You will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445A (Rev. 5/23/94)Y IMPORTANT - PLEASE SEE REVERSE
